  <teaser>The advent of 5G has completely transformed the telecommunications landscape, elevating the wireless experience to unprecedented heights. However, the key challenge associated with 5G deployment is the substantial increase in the number of required radios which translates to...</teaser>
  <objective><![CDATA[The advent of 5G has completely transformed the telecommunications landscape, elevating the wireless experience to unprecedented heights. However, the key challenge associated with 5G deployment is the substantial increase in the number of required radios which translates to high CAPEX & OPEX. The transition from the passive to active antenna concept, packing tenths of radios in a Radio Unit, is contributing to both increased intricacy & expenses. The Argo Active Antenna Catalyst enables a single board RU, which represents a groundbreaking integration of RF Integrated Circuit (RFIC) with Ultra Slim Printed Antenna Array. Our path reduction RFIC leads to increased flexibility in network deployment which can be leveraged to enhance cost-effectiveness, reduce power consumption, and expand coverage. With EIC support, we intend to finalize the optimization, manufacturing & validation of our RFIC, commercialize ‘Argo Active Antenna Catalyst’ as a comprehensive solution & scale-up globally.]]></objective>
  <title>Development finalization and optimization of Argo Semi Active Antenna Catalyst to revolutionize sub-6GHz 5G wireless systems</title>
